{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":120201,"duration_api_ms":107668,"num_turns":16,"result":"**Review: Approved**\n\nThe implementation correctly addresses the original problem. Key findings:\n\n1. **Core bug fixed**: Non-zero exit paths no longer call `cleanup()` after preserving failure artifacts. The old `preserve_failure_artifacts` + `cleanup()` two-step (which deleted preserved files) is replaced by a single `cleanup_failed_invocation()` call.\n\n2. **Artifact preservation works correctly**: Codex temp files (schema, last-message) are moved to `runtime/failed/`, and a `.failed.raw` file with formatted stdout+stderr is written. `best_effort_move_file` has a copy+delete fallback for cross-device scenarios and preserves originals if the move fails entirely.\n\n3. **No regressions**: All 26 unit tests pass, including 3 new tests covering the happy path (artifacts moved), fallback path (originals preserved when move fails), and success cleanup (temp files still deleted normally).\n\n4. **Clean rename**: No stale references to the old `preserve_failure_artifacts` name remain in the codebase.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"61597a50-b963-4c21-8efb-6138899fa499","total_cost_usd":0.36761,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":28328,"cache_read_input_tokens":238220,"output_tokens":2856,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":28328,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":10,"outputTokens":2856,"cacheReadInputTokens":238220,"cacheCreationInputTokens":28328,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.36761,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"evidence":["Renamed `preserve_failure_artifacts` to `cleanup_failed_invocation` — no stale references remain (grep confirmed).","Non-zero exit paths at lines 877-879 and 900 now call `cleanup_failed_invocation` WITHOUT a subsequent `cleanup()` call, fixing the original bug where temp files were deleted after preservation.","The `finish()` error paths (lines 107, 125, 150, 199, 211) correctly call `cleanup_failed_invocation` — since `finish` consumes `self`, no cleanup can follow.","`cleanup_failed_invocation` moves schema/last-message files into `runtime/failed/` via `best_effort_move_file`, writes `<id>.failed.raw` with formatted stdout+stderr, and gracefully handles failures (file-not-found is ignored, copy+delete fallback for cross-device moves).","`best_effort_move_file` preserves originals if the move/copy fails (no silent deletion of evidence).","`format_failed_raw_output` produces a clear `=== stdout ===\\n...\\n=== stderr ===\\n...\\n` format with newline normalization.","`cleanup()` (success path) remains unchanged — still deletes temp files — and is only called on successful invocations or pre-retry cleanup.","All 26 `adapters::process_backend::tests` pass, including 3 new tests: artifact move on failure, fallback preservation when move fails, and success cleanup.","New helper `make_failed_child_output` correctly constructs an ExitStatus with code 1 via `from_raw(1 << 8)` (Unix convention for wait status).","Claude decoder's `cleanup_failed_invocation` arm is a no-op for file moves (`ResponseDecoder::Claude { .. } => {}`) but still writes the `.failed.raw` file — correct behavior since Claude has no temp files to move."],"findings_or_gaps":["Minor: `cleanup_failed_invocation` writes `.failed.raw` even for the Claude decoder, which has no temp files to move. While benign (raw output is still useful for debugging), it means the Claude path creates a `runtime/failed/` directory and a `.failed.raw` file that wasn't explicitly in scope. This is arguably a net positive for operator inspection.","The `best_effort_move_file` NotFound case silently succeeds — if the temp file was already gone before the move, no error is raised and no `.failed.raw` content references the missing file. Acceptable for best-effort semantics but worth noting.","No integration/end-to-end test was run (implementer noted this limitation due to environment constraints). Unit test coverage is solid but doesn't exercise the full `invoke()` method through a real process spawn."],"follow_up_or_amendments":[],"outcome":"approved"},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"88bd3413-7e25-465b-bcc1-e9277025f8c6"}
